<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>standard pickup group</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
average level 63.<br>
for example :<br>
62 Tank <br>
63 cleric<br>
64 rogue<br>
65 mage (me)<br>
60 shaman<br>
<br>
around 20/22 kills an hour, 33 pct AA<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>very good group</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
I spent 1 hour and half with a very good group in INNER<br>
Warrior 65 (from the ubuest guild of our server)<br>
65 SK<br>
62 cleric<br>
65 Mage<br>
65 Shaman<br>
65 Bard<br>
<br>
32 kills an hour for 50 % AA <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>kitting group</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
65 shaman, SK, mage but first time we are trying that, place : outer<br>
13 kill an hour, 27 pct XP <br>
<br>
with same people but more trained, we can have an average percentage between standard group and uber one.<br>
<br>
...<br>
<br>
now some people told me, in this forum, that they were able to have an AA/Hour, I don't know how they manage. <br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/citation/signat.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Equipment : <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=159910">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=159910</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=magnasab>MagnasAB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#333333>(2/28/03 4:02:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Stats : AA in POV</span><hr size=1> Ailees what camp were you at.  Other then Inner Cave the exp in PoV is really not all that good at level 65.  Groups in BoT or even PoS at giants will net you much better Exp.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailees>Ailees</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/maitres/ailees.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 921<br> <font color=#333333>(2/28/03 7:56:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/citation/tov.jpg WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=160></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Stats : AA in POV</span><hr size=1> I went to POV this week to be sure I <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">have allways same kind of mob</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->. <br>
Some people in here have writen that a good fighting group can do 1AA/Hour and I thought it was a false idea. Now I am sure it is. <br>
Our &quot;uber&quot; group was not the best you can do, but was really very good ! cleric was obliged to nuke because he had nothing to do : bard song was enough to help tank, and mana song was enough to let me nuke 4 BS each mob.<br>
<br>
Places ?<br>
inner, outer, east and west castle walls.<br>
Results have been more or less same, and I just gave 2 examples. The &quot;uber&quot; one was made at inner. <br>
But all week long I could see that each kill (full group) gives <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>1.5 AA XP.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and then it all depends on how fast you pull/kill.<br>
<br>
Of course BOT XP is much better (but not &quot;much&quot;), but you also loose much more time, and finding a group in there is not easy ! (I have to wait for mezz and charm).<br>
<br>
I want to go to HOH and make some stats. As far as I already saw, XP is better, but nothing really extraordinary. I did not spend hours counting, then I can't say exactly. May be 2 AA XP each kill, which is already 33% better.<br>
<br>
I am going to do same testing in here, but it is much longer : I must find a group first, and that's often a pita. Next stats will be with HOH kitting.<br>
<br>
<br>
